<tf desc="mc" ref="fb3" fs="13" x="1067.45" y="118.85" wi="301" he="56">
The height sensor detects the actual level and transmits this value as electrical signal to the ECU.</tf>
<tf desc="mc" ref="fb4" fs="13" x="1066.45" y="185.85" wi="363" he="59">
During control processes the solenoid valve increases or decreases the air pressure in the air suspension below according to the signals of the ECAS ECU.</tf>
<tf desc="mc" ref="fb5" fs="13" x="1065.45" y="250.85" wi="272" he="43">
During a control process the air suspension bellow raises and lowers the superstructure.</tf>
